1
00:00:07,541 --> 00:00:13,500
[Music]

2
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:40,458
I'm Takumi Nishijo...

3
00:01:40,541 --> 00:01:42,708
Sena, Kozzy and
I teamed up

4
00:01:42,791 --> 00:01:44,875
and went after the
Nozomi Group,

5
00:01:44,958 --> 00:01:47,541
a powerful company that is
trying to recreate the ability

6
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:48,833
of the gigalomaniacs

7
00:01:48,916 --> 00:01:51,125
and use it for
evil purposes.

8
00:01:51,208 --> 00:01:54,083
However, company president
Genichi Norose

9
00:01:54,166 --> 00:01:56,375
was immediately
on to our plan.

10
00:01:56,458 --> 00:01:58,875
He used the power of
Noah II's prototype

11
00:01:58,958 --> 00:02:02,208
to make Sena and
Kozzy suffer...

12
00:02:02,291 --> 00:02:04,208
He also tried his
best to kill me.

13
00:02:05,666 --> 00:02:07,375
Suddenly a miracle
happened...

14
00:02:07,458 --> 00:02:09,791
Ayase showed up and
came to our rescue.

15
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:15,291
But the Norose we fought
so hard to beat...

16
00:02:15,375 --> 00:02:16,750
It was a delusion.

17
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:31,458
I'm so sorry, I hope you
haven't been waiting too long.

18
00:02:31,541 --> 00:02:34,083
I'm Ban, Shibuya Police.

19
00:02:34,166 --> 00:02:36,500
Your name's Yua
Kusunoki, right?

20
00:02:36,583 --> 00:02:37,625
Yes.

21
00:02:37,708 --> 00:02:39,750
You're related to
Mia Kusunoki...

22
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:42,125
The young girl who died in
the first New Gen crime,

23
00:02:42,208 --> 00:02:44,125
known commonly as
the "Group Dive"...

24
00:02:44,208 --> 00:02:46,791
You two were twin
sisters, correct?

25
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,250
Well to bring you
up to speed...

26
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:50,041
Yua here has been
investigating

27
00:02:50,125 --> 00:02:52,458
the New Gen incidents
all on her own...

28
00:02:52,541 --> 00:02:55,125
She's trying to find out what
happened to her sister...

29
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:57,375
That must've been really
difficult for her.

30
00:02:57,458 --> 00:03:00,375
That's not all. She's narrowed
it down to one suspect.

31
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:02,333
It's Takumi Nishijo.

32
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:05,750
That's interesting...

33
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,500
Very much so.

34
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:10,000
So what exactly led
you to this conclusion?

35
00:03:10,958 --> 00:03:12,166
Just give me one sec.

36
00:03:14,791 --> 00:03:16,166
I gotta take this call.

37
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:17,958
Yeah, this is
Ban, what's up?

38
00:03:18,041 --> 00:03:19,416
It's number six...!

39
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,458
The sixth New Gen incident
was just reported!

40
00:03:22,541 --> 00:03:23,583
What was that?

41
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:27,291
The sixth case?!

42
00:03:27,375 --> 00:03:28,500
No,. it can't be...

43
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:29,958
Hey what's wrong?

44
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:34,916
Each of the three victims'
bodies were severed,

45
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,083
all of them cut in half
at the waist...

46
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:39,125
Their upper and
lower bodies were...

47
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:40,666
all sewn up

48
00:03:40,750 --> 00:03:43,166
and then stitched back together
again with fishing line...

49
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:44,666
There were wounds
on their bodies

50
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:46,958
resembling the letters
"D," "Q" and "N."

51
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:49,375
So gruesome.

52
00:03:49,458 --> 00:03:50,500
I know these guys!

53
00:03:50,583 --> 00:03:52,041
What do you mean?

54
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:55,375
Well, they, uh-They picked a
fight with me a while back.

55
00:03:55,458 --> 00:03:56,666
It's the General...

56
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:59,708
He's provoking me
again, I know it!

57
00:03:59,791 --> 00:04:01,500
Hey don't worry.

58
00:04:01,583 --> 00:04:03,541
I'm sure it's just
a coincidence.

59
00:04:03,625 --> 00:04:04,833
Plus...

60
00:04:04,916 --> 00:04:06,750
I am so hungry
I can't think...

61
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:08,875
You wanna go grab
a bite to eat...?

62
00:04:08,958 --> 00:04:11,708
I know an awesome place
that's super cheap.

63
00:04:11,791 --> 00:04:14,166
Just give me a break...!

64
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,666
This whole thing is
driving me insane!

65
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:17,791
You got it...

66
00:04:17,875 --> 00:04:19,375
You're in charge of
the crime scene...

67
00:04:19,458 --> 00:04:20,541
I'd come, but I think

68
00:04:20,625 --> 00:04:22,708
I'm onto a very important
lead right now.

69
00:04:22,791 --> 00:04:23,875
Roger.

70
00:04:25,875 --> 00:04:27,500
You may end up
opening Pandora's box

71
00:04:27,583 --> 00:04:29,000
