For example, have you
ever seen anybody

112
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:31,041
pull a big sword
out of thin air?

113
00:06:31,125 --> 00:06:33,166
How do you know about her?

114
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:34,666
Do you know her name?

115
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:36,875
Yes, Ayase Kishimoto.

116
00:06:36,958 --> 00:06:38,583
I saw her do it...

117
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:40,000
It was incredible,

118
00:06:40,083 --> 00:06:42,000
she pulled a sword
out of nowhere.

119
00:06:42,083 --> 00:06:43,750
I saw the exact same thing

120
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:45,416
done by another
girl named Sena.

121
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:47,000
Huh?

122
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:49,666
Several reports have been
submitted by concerned citizens

123
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:53,125
who have seen this girl carrying
a sword all over the city.

124
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:55,083
Yes, but... that's not all...

125
00:06:55,166 --> 00:06:57,583
I saw Ayase split in two.

126
00:06:57,666 --> 00:06:59,750
Just like that,
there were two of her!

127
00:07:01,458 --> 00:07:03,541
I've already confirmed
that Ayase and Sena

128
00:07:03,625 --> 00:07:05,875
have separately made contact
with Takumi Nishijo

129
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:07,333
in the past few days.

130
00:07:07,416 --> 00:07:10,000
Takumi.

131
00:07:10,083 --> 00:07:11,500
I may not be able
to explain it,

132
00:07:11,583 --> 00:07:13,041
but everywhere that boy goes,

133
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:16,500
strange and mysterious things
seem to be right behind him.

134
00:07:16,583 --> 00:07:18,000
Oh, by the way, Yua...

135
00:07:18,083 --> 00:07:20,125
Those little charmy things
hanging from your bag...

136
00:07:20,208 --> 00:07:21,541
Those are the
Hoppy the Frog dolls

137
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:23,541
that are so popular with
all the kids, aren't they?

138
00:07:23,625 --> 00:07:25,625
Oh yeah.

139
00:07:25,708 --> 00:07:26,916
I think I'd like one.

140
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,750
Would you mind
picking one up for me?

141
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:30,416
Of course,
I'd be happy to.

142
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:32,250
What the hell's
Hoppy the Frog?

143
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:33,541
It's a teenager thing,

144
00:07:33,625 --> 00:07:36,333
a few specialty shops
in town sell them... Duh.

145
00:07:36,416 --> 00:07:38,375
On Fridays kids line up
all the way around the block

146
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,625
to get one.

147
00:07:39,708 --> 00:07:41,125
On Fridays, huh?

148
00:07:41,208 --> 00:07:43,041
Yep, every Friday
new designs come out.

149
00:07:43,125 --> 00:07:44,875
People look forward
to it all week long.

150
00:07:44,958 --> 00:07:46,583
You thinking
the same thing?

151
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:48,583
Hoppy the Frog sales
aren't the only thing

152
00:07:48,666 --> 00:07:50,833
spiking on the weekend.

153
00:07:50,916 --> 00:07:52,791
Let's check this thing out.

154
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:56,458
Taku...

155
00:07:56,541 --> 00:07:57,583
Hey, Taku!

156
00:07:58,750 --> 00:07:59,916
Where the heck
is Ayase's room?

157
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,208
I've got no clue.

158
00:08:01,291 --> 00:08:02,958
This is the
outpatient ward...

159
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:04,416
In-patients
are over there.

160
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:06,166
What are you,
a tour guide...?

161
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:08,958
You sure know a lot
about this place.

162
00:08:09,041 --> 00:08:10,875
Well at least somebody
knows what's going on...

163
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:12,333
You invited us to come,

164
00:08:12,416 --> 00:08:13,833
you should at
least know the way.

165
00:08:13,916 --> 00:08:15,625
Actually, I only
invited Taku...

166
00:08:15,708 --> 00:08:17,583
You just decided
to crash the party.

167
00:08:17,666 --> 00:08:18,791
Did I really?

168
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:21,750
Well, I'm going
to the bathroom,

169
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,666
you guys go on ahead,
I'll catch up with you later.

170
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:24,791
Cool.

171
00:08:32,291 --> 00:08:33,833
Where do you
think she went?

172
00:08:33,916 --> 00:08:35,000
Hell, I don't know.

173
00:08:37,625 --> 00:08:39,041
The "Gladiale Saga"?

174
00:08:39,125 --> 00:08:40,958
It looks like a
fantasy novel.

175
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:43,250
If I'm going to make
Ayase fall in love with me,

176
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:45,583
I'm probably gonna have to
read this book, aren't I?

177
00:08:45,666 --> 00:08:48,750
I guess Ayase's well
enough to walk then.

178
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,125
By the way,
do you think

179
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:51,583
Rimi's gonna be able
to find this room?

180
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:53,416
Huh?

181
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,916
Rimi's not exactly the
smartest person I've ever met,

182
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,833
so I highly doubt it
occurred to her to stop

183
00:08:57,916 --> 00:08:59,583
and ask somebody
for assistance.

184
00:08:59,666 --> 00:09:00,791
We should go find her.

185
00:09:00,875 --> 00:09:03,125
Hey wait a second.

186
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:04,708
That thing I heard
about you and Ayase

187
00:09:04,791 --> 00:09:07,791
sleeping together was
just a rumor, right?

188
00:09:07,875 --> 00:09:10,875
I mean, you look so lonely
when Rimi's not by your side.

189
00:09:13,083 --> 00:09:14,958
Well... I'll check downstairs.

190
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:16,000
Then I'll go up.

191
00:09:37,083 --> 00:09:38,958
Why do I feel this way,

192
00:09:39,041 --> 00:09:40,416
like I shouldn't be here?

193
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:50,625
What is this place?

194
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:56,500
Oh no...

195
00:09:56,583 --> 00:09:57,666
No!

196
00:10:01,541 --> 00:10:02,500
The General...

197
00:10:02,583 --> 00:10:04,416
He's reading my
thoughts again...!

198
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:07,000
I wanna go home!

199
00:10:07,083 --> 00:10:09,000
May the divine
light save you...

200
00:10:09,083 --> 00:10:11,166
May the divine
light defend you...

201
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:13,208
May the divine
light protect you...

202
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:15,125
May the divine
light cleanse you.

203
00:10:17,458 --> 00:10:18,625
Oh wow...

204
00:10:18,708 --> 00:10:21,041
Takumi is a full-blown
anime nerd, isn't he?

205
00:10:22,916 --> 00:10:25,958
Takumi Nishijo
is not normal.

206
00:10:26,041 --> 00:10:29,041
What if somebody is giving
him artificial support...?

207
00:10:29,125 --> 00:10:30,375
What will we do?

208
00:10:36,416 --> 00:10:37,750
Cool...

209
00:10:37,833 --> 00:10:39,458
"Those eyes,
whose are they?"...

210
00:10:39,541 --> 00:10:43,083
I guess Takumi really is the
"Whose eyes" guy after all.

211
00:10:43,166 --> 00:10:45,458
I knew it was
him all along!

212
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:47,208
No way.

213
00:10:47,291 --> 00:10:49,500
"Ir2"?

214
00:10:49,583 --> 00:10:50,583
Well, what's that?

215
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:53,125
Are you okay?

216
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:57,833
What in the
world was that?

217
00:10:57,916 --> 00:10:59,416
Hey, Taku.

218
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:01,208
You don't look so good...

219
00:11:01,291 --> 00:11:05,125
But I guess you
never really do, huh?

220
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:06,833
I found Rimi and Ayase.

221
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:09,250
Look right down there.

222
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:18,625
What was that
all about...?

223
00:11:18,708 --> 00:11:21,208
Do those two hold
some kind of grudge?

224
00:11:21,291 --> 00:11:22,416
Anyway...

225
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:24,333
Let's pretend we
didn't see that.

226
00:11:24,416 --> 00:11:25,458
Yeah.

227
00:11:28,166 --> 00:11:29,250
Yo, Ayase!

228
00:11:30,916 --> 00:11:31,750
Just thought you'd
like to know,

229
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,166
you look hot in your PJs...

230
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:34,583
Right, Taku?

231
00:11:45,583 --> 00:11:46,791
How do you feel...?

232
00:11:46,875 --> 00:11:48,125
You sure do look a
whole lot better.

233
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:50,250
Hey...! Ayase...

234
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:51,625
Do you like books...?

235
00:11:51,708 --> 00:11:52,708
I'm reading one that's
called the Gladiale Saga...

236
00:11:52,791 --> 00:11:54,625
Takumi... You do realize

237
00:11:54,708 --> 00:11:56,375
you're one of the
Seven Knights of Gladiale.

238
00:11:58,125 --> 00:12:00,375
You have a great
wickedness inside of you...

239
00:12:00,458 --> 00:12:03,041
That's what makes you
an ideal Black Knight...

240
00:12:03,125 --> 00:12:05,250
It's why you've
been chosen...

241
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:07,125
All the pain and suffering
you're experiencing

242
00:12:07,208 --> 00:12:08,541
is divine punishment...

243
00:12:08,625 --> 00:12:11,250
