00:12:54,208 --> 00:12:56,458
You don't know what a
gigalomaniac is...?

266
00:12:56,541 --> 00:12:58,125
That girl Sena
told me about it.

267
00:12:58,208 --> 00:13:00,083
Oh, that girl,
I know her...

268
00:13:00,166 --> 00:13:01,750
She is a Knight
of Gladiale too,

269
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:03,166
just like you and I are.

270
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,208
Listen to me,
I am not a knight...

271
00:13:05,291 --> 00:13:06,208
I'm not...

272
00:13:06,291 --> 00:13:07,750
I don't have a di-sword...

273
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:09,125
I've got nothing.

274
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:10,958
It's your divine
punishment...

275
00:13:11,041 --> 00:13:13,666
Once you overcome it,
your sword will be revealed.

276
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:15,291
Punishment?

277
00:13:15,375 --> 00:13:16,458
Your suffering...

278
00:13:16,541 --> 00:13:18,166
The explosion of
emotional burdens

279
00:13:18,250 --> 00:13:20,583
burying themselves deep
inside your mind...

280
00:13:20,666 --> 00:13:21,625
In other words...

281
00:13:21,708 --> 00:13:24,708
Psychological torture.

282
00:13:24,791 --> 00:13:26,083
I experienced it...

283
00:13:37,166 --> 00:13:39,083
The drops of water
fell into my eyes

284
00:13:39,166 --> 00:13:41,750
in precisely
five-second intervals.

285
00:13:41,833 --> 00:13:43,333
It went on like that...

286
00:13:43,416 --> 00:13:45,666
for two weeks without
a moment's rest.

287
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:53,416
The instant before my
mind was about to break...

288
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:56,041
I could hear the voice
of the Great Will.

289
00:13:56,125 --> 00:13:58,125
And I was finally
able to summon it.

290
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:01,250
That was divine
punishment...

291
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:03,375
In order to get the power
to defeat the demon,

292
00:14:03,458 --> 00:14:06,625
you have to purify your own,
and cleanse it from within.

293
00:14:06,708 --> 00:14:08,250
What are you saying...?

294
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:11,041
That I have to keep
on suffering...?

295
00:14:11,125 --> 00:14:13,083
I don't want to do this...

296
00:14:13,166 --> 00:14:15,458
Please, I just want
to be left alone!

297
00:14:15,541 --> 00:14:17,291
It's all a revelation.

298
00:14:17,375 --> 00:14:18,833
We're running
out of time,

299
00:14:18,916 --> 00:14:21,208
the Seven Knights should've
already gathered in this city...

300
00:14:21,291 --> 00:14:23,208
The moment has come,
they must awaken!

301
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,000
If we don't do
something quickly,

302
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:28,916
the world will fall to
ruin by Gladiale's hand.

303
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,208
I'm sorry, guys...

304
00:14:30,291 --> 00:14:31,916
I didn't know where
the hospital room was,

305
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:34,541
so I got lost
wandering around.

306
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:36,833
So... Did you
get to see Ayase?

307
00:14:36,916 --> 00:14:39,375
Yeah, but I don't really
care about Ayase anymore.

308
00:14:41,166 --> 00:14:43,208
She's way too
crazy for me...

309
00:14:43,291 --> 00:14:45,708
Plus I don't like
fantasy novels.

310
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:47,250
Did something happen?

311
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:49,083
Oh yeah...
You could say that.

312
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,166
Another prank call?

313
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:58,791
Hey, Nanami, cut it out!

314
00:14:58,875 --> 00:15:00,541
Taku...

315
00:15:00,625 --> 00:15:03,166
Where am I?

316
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:04,500
Please help me...

317
00:15:04,583 --> 00:15:06,291
I wanna go home!

318
00:15:06,375 --> 00:15:07,291
Nana...

319
00:15:11,083 --> 00:15:12,750
This place is dead...

320
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:14,791
Guess there aren't a lot of
customers before the weekend.

321
00:15:14,875 --> 00:15:16,083
Yeah...

322
00:15:16,166 --> 00:15:17,458
It's 'cause it's the
middle of the week.

323
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:20,083
From Friday to Sunday it's
pretty crowded in here.

324
00:15:20,166 --> 00:15:22,083
Um... In other words...

325
00:15:22,166 --> 00:15:24,250
it's not usually very
busy until the weekend

326
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:26,250
when a new Hoppy
gets released.

327
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:28,583
So it only happens
on the weekends, eh?

328
00:15:28,666 --> 00:15:30,208
Oh... look!

329
00:15:30,291 --> 00:15:31,125
What's wrong?

330
00:15:33,166 --> 00:15:34,958
That must be the new
Floppy the Frog

331
00:15:35,041 --> 00:15:36,458
that goes on sale tomorrow.

332
00:15:36,541 --> 00:15:38,291
Uh... Actually,
it's Hoppy the Frog.

333
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:40,458
Well, well, looky there...

334
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:42,250
The Shinko Corporation.

335
00:15:43,958 --> 00:15:45,750
I'm worried
about Nanami...

336
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:47,666
What if it wasn't a prank?

337
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:49,125
What's the matter, Taku?

338
00:15:49,208 --> 00:15:51,041
You're acting a
little weird...

339
00:15:51,125 --> 00:15:52,916
Is everything okay?

340
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,958
I'm just a little bit
worried about my sister.

341
00:15:55,041 --> 00:15:56,958
I think I should go
home and check on her.

342
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:58,416
Oh... So you're going home?

343
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,250
Yeah... Would you
come with me please...

344
00:16:00,333 --> 00:16:02,125
I really don't wanna
go there alone.

345
00:16:05,041 --> 00:16:06,083
Sena?

346
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:08,291
Are you the one who
drew this picture?

347
00:16:08,375 --> 00:16:09,583
Answer me!

348
00:16:09,666 --> 00:16:11,708
What in the world is
she doing with that?

349
00:16:11,791 --> 00:16:13,791
I asked you a question!

350
00:16:13,875 --> 00:16:16,000
Yeah, I did, so what?

351
00:16:16,083 --> 00:16:18,208
Takumi, run, now!

352
00:16:19,708 --> 00:16:20,583
Prepare yourself!

353
00:16:20,666 --> 00:16:21,791
Look out!

354
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:25,166
Why is Sena attacking me?

355
00:16:27,958 --> 00:16:29,958
Wait, what did I do wrong?

356
00:16:32,375 --> 00:16:34,041
Rimi.

357
00:16:34,125 --> 00:16:35,041
Move!

358
00:16:35,125 --> 00:16:36,875
Stop it... Stop it!

359
00:16:39,708 --> 00:16:41,250
What the hell is this?!

360
00:16:43,541 --> 00:16:44,750
Rimi is one of us.

361
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:47,041
She's a gigalomaniac, too!

362
00:16:47,125 --> 00:16:49,333
Stop it, you
leave him alone!

363
00:16:49,416 --> 00:16:51,541
But don't you realize what
this idiot created...?

364
00:16:51,625 --> 00:16:53,625
He's responsible for
the IR2 equation!

365
00:16:53,708 --> 00:16:54,791
Yes, I know.

366
00:16:54,875 --> 00:16:55,916
Then move.

367
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,625
If you cause
him to awaken,

368
00:16:57,708 --> 00:16:59,500
things won't
get any better.

369
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:01,708
I'll kill him before that.

370
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:03,541
You won't be able to.

371
00:17:18,625 --> 00:17:19,916
Sena.

372
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,416
It's you.

373
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,083
I finally found you.

374
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,750
I didn't know
what else to do...

375
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:42,208
I had no other alternative

376
00:17:42,291 --> 00:17:44,125
but to offer your
mother as a sacrifice,

377
00:17:44,208 --> 00:17:45,500
can't you understand that?

378
00:17:45,583 --> 00:17:46,791
Shut up.

379
00:17:46,875 --> 00:17:48,125
Because of your mother,

380
00:17:48,208 --> 00:17:50,250
we were able to achieve
unparalleled results...

381
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:52,375
Her death was useful
in our experiments.

382
00:17:52,458 --> 00:17:53,416
Shut the hell up!

383
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:03,458
At last...

384
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:05,083
I've finally avenged her.

385
00:18:06,208 --> 00:18:07,250
Sena.

386
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:09,583
No, stop it...!

387
00:18:09,666 --> 00:18:12,208
Please let go of me!

388
00:18:12,291 --> 00:18:13,708
It's okay.

389
00:18:13,791 --> 00:18:15,250
No... Let go...

390
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:16,708
I don't want this.

391
00:18:16,791 --> 00:18:19,333
But this is the delusion
that you wished for.

392
00:18:22,166 --> 00:18:23,083
Sena!

393
00:18:26,875 --> 00:18:29,083
I'm sorry for causing
you all this pain...

394
00:18:29,166 --> 00:18:31,166
But you left me
no other option.

395
00:18:35,708 --> 00:18:37,625
Did Rimi just
do that to her?

396
00:18:37,708 --> 00:18:39,083
It's over now, right...?

397
00:18:39,166 --> 00:18:41,083
You'll leave her be,
won't you, Rimi?

398
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:42,916
If you're a big
meanie head to Sena

399
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,250
and try to cause
her any more pain,

400
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:47,500
I promise I'll never
ever forgive you.

401
00:18:47,583 --> 00:18:49,416
It's all over
now, I swear.

402
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:51,041
I really didn't
want to hurt her,

403
00:18:51,125 --> 00:18:52,791
that was never
my intention...

404
00:18:52,875 --> 00:18:54,708
If she promises to
keep away from Taku,

405
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:56,041
then I'll leave her alone.

406
00:18:56,125 --> 00:18:57,416
That's not gonna work...

407
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:59,125
It's just not possible...

408
00:18:59,208 --> 00:19:01,000
I mean, the three
of us are friends.

409
00:19:01,083 --> 00:19:03,083
We do stuff together
all the time, right?

410
00:19:03,166 --> 00:19:04,166
Right...?

411
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:06,000
Tell her how
it is, Takumi.

412
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:10,791
Because of what you've done,
my family is ruined!

413
00:19:10,875 --> 00:19:12,625
Whadda you mean,
your family?

414
00:19:17,541 --> 00:19:18,833
The formula you created,

415
00:19:18,916 --> 00:19:21,000
it has potential to
destroy the world...

416
00:19:21,083 --> 00:19:22,500
It's the most
dangerous equation

417
00:19:22,583 --> 00:19:24,166
that has ever
been conceived...

418
00:19:24,250 --> 00:19:25,458
And it's the cause
of all the chaos

419
00:19:25,541 --> 00:19:27,416
that's assaulting our city!

420
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,791
Equation?

421
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:29,625
Don't say any more.

422
00:19:29,708 --> 00:19:30,833
Just drop it.

423
00:19:30,916 --> 00:19:32,416
But what do you mean?

424
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,875
Hey is this it...?

425
00:19:33,958 --> 00:19:34,958
The formula?

426
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:40,541
That's just a drawing,
it's nothing!

427
00:19:40,625 --> 00:19:43,458
F U N to the tenth
power times I N T

428
00:19:43,541 --> 00:19:46,583
to the fortieth power
equals... I R two.

429
00:19:46,666 --> 00:19:48,333
The moment you
created this equation

430
00:19:48,416 --> 00:19:49,708
the world split in two...

431
00:19:49,791 --> 00:19:51,041
You destroyed everything!

432
00:19:55,250 --> 00:19:57,875
This equation is the principal
mathematical component

433
00:19:57,958 --> 00:19:59,958
behind the functionality
of Noah II.

434
00:20:00,041 --> 00:20:01,583
The formula is
incorporated

435
00:20:01,666 --> 00:20:03,333
into the core of
the system...

436
00:20:03,416 --> 00:20:07,166
Remarkably, we discovered it in
the most unusual of places.

437
00:20:07,250 --> 00:20:10,208
A young child scribbled
it while drawing...

438
00:20:10,291 --> 00:20:12,041
Yes, "IR two"...

439
00:20:12,125 --> 00:20:13,500
Thanks to this
simple equation,

440
00:20:13,583 --> 00:20:15,875
Noah II's mechanism was
taken to the next level,

441
00:20:15,958 --> 00:20:17,083
its hardware achieving

442
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:19,541
what you might call
god-like ability.

443
00:20:19,625 --> 00:20:20,833
Now all we have to do

444
00:20:20,916 --> 00:20:23,291
is continue to gather
gigalomaniac code samples

445
00:20:23,375 --> 00:20:24,833
for Noah II's software,

446
00:20:24,916 --> 00:20:27,750
and the program will begin to
operate at full capacity...

447
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,041
just like that.

448
00:20:29,125 --> 00:20:30,250
How many samples
have you gathered?

449
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:31,750
Where do we stand?

450
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:33,625
I have already
secured samples

451
00:20:33,708 --> 00:20:35,166
from five different people.

452
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:37,208
Then things are
right on track.

453
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:38,333
But remember this,

454
00:20:38,416 --> 00:20:40,208
the more samples
we can get...

455
00:20:40,291 --> 00:20:42,791
the more powerful the
Noah II will become...

456
00:20:42,875 --> 00:20:44,083
With your permission,

457
00:20:44,166 --> 00:20:46,208
there is one gigalomaniac
boy in particular

458
00:20:46,291 --> 00:20:48,583
whose sample I am
planning on collecting.

459
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:49,958
That's fine,

460
00:20:50,041 --> 00:20:52,000
so long as it does not
cause a delay in our plans.

461
00:20:52,083 --> 00:20:54,625
How long until Noah
II's fully operational?

462
00:20:54,708 --> 00:20:56,041
Before we move on,

463
00:20:56,125 --> 00:20:58,333
I must conduct one
final experiment...

464
00:20:58,416 --> 00:21:00,416
I will initiate
the third melt.

465
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,875
Wait, the third melt?

466
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:03,541
I believe it will be
on the level of the

467
00:21:03,625 --> 00:21:05,458
Great Kanto Earthquake.

468
00:21:05,541 --> 00:21:07,916
The Kanto Earthquake,
are you serious?

469
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,416
That was the greatest
natural disaster

470
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:10,708
this country has seen.

471
00:21:10,791 --> 00:21:12,041
After the third melt

472
00:21:12,125 --> 00:21:13,625
successfully achieves
its result,

473
00:21:13,708 --> 00:21:15,583
Noah II will have
attained near perfection

474
00:21:15,666 --> 00:21:17,208
in its final form...

475
00:21:17,291 --> 00:21:21,041
The world's possibilities
will be in our hands.

476
00:21:21,125 --> 00:21:22,166
IR2...

477
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:25,208
The formula that
creates silent weapons.

478
00:21:25,291 --> 00:21:27,500
But what are the
silent weapons?

479
00:21:27,583 --> 00:21:28,791
Mind reading...

480
00:21:28,875 --> 00:21:30,125
Visual projection...

481
00:21:30,208 --> 00:21:31,833
Sensory control...

482
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:33,291
With this...

483
00:21:33,375 --> 00:21:36,458
gigalomaniacs will never
be special beings again...

484
00:21:36,541 --> 00:21:38,416
This power will be
available to anyone

485
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:41,208
to use indiscriminately.

486
00:21:41,291 --> 00:21:43,208
And it is all thanks
to the Noah II machine

487
00:21:43,291 --> 00:21:44,958
derived from
your equation.

488
00:21:45,041 --> 00:21:46,208
The Noah II.

489
00:21:46,291 --> 00:21:47,750
We saw it!

490
00:21:47,833 --> 00:21:49,125
What's worse...

491
00:21:49,208 --> 00:21:51,625
People will never
know about this...

492
00:21:51,708 --> 00:21:54,083
Norose and those corrupt
bastards will monopolize it

493
00:21:54,166 --> 00:21:55,791
before people
ever realize.

494
00:21:55,875 --> 00:21:58,875
But that's got
nothing to do with me!

495
00:21:58,958 --> 00:22:00,250
Look I'm not to
blame for this,

496
00:22:00,333 --> 00:22:01,791
I didn't hurt anybody!

497
00:22:01,875 --> 00:22:04,208
If I don't even remember
writing the stupid thing

498
00:22:04,291 --> 00:22:05,875
then how can
it be my fault?

499
00:22:05,958 --> 00:22:07,708
None of this
really matters.

500
00:22:07,791 --> 00:22:08,958
The important thing
is the person

501
00:22:09,041 --> 00:22:11,208
who came up with the
"Those eyes" phrase.

502
00:22:11,291 --> 00:22:13,875
And that's you, Takumi,
you made it up...!

503
00:22:13,958 --> 00:22:17,541
See, the old man knew exactly
what he was talking about!

504
00:22:17,625 --> 00:22:18,666
What's that...?

505
00:22:18,750 --> 00:22:20,416
What old man are
you talking about?

506
00:22:20,500 --> 00:22:21,791
Well, let's see.

507
00:22:21,875 --> 00:22:23,875
He was the person who
originally told me

508
00:22:23,958 --> 00:22:25,750
how important
di-swords were.

509
00:22:28,875 --> 00:22:30,791
I remember him 'cause he
was the first one in town

510
00:22:30,875 --> 00:22:32,958
to speak to me.

511
00:22:33,041 --> 00:22:35,250
Why didn't you tell me
about this sooner, Kozue?!

512
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:36,250
I'm sorry!

513
00:22:36,333 --> 00:22:37,916
How was I
supposed to know?

514
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,166
It's true...

515
00:22:39,250 --> 00:22:41,666
He's really in this city.

516
00:22:41,750 --> 00:22:43,791
I'll finally get
my revenge...

517
00:22:43,875 --> 00:22:45,166
Finally...

518
00:22:45,250 --> 00:22:46,833
I will kill him!

519
00:22:52,208 --> 00:22:53,625
I'm sorry...

520
00:22:53,708 --> 00:22:55,083
I'm sorry I lied.

521
00:22:59,208 --> 00:23:01,500
I don't even know
who you are anymore.

522
00:23:01,583 --> 00:23:03,083
Taku...

523
00:23:03,166 --> 00:23:04,666
I think of myself
as your friend,

524
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:05,958
I don't want to lose you...

525
00:23:06,041 --> 00:23:08,333
Please just trust me.

526
00:23:08,416 --> 00:23:10,083
Rimi.

527
00:23:10,166 --> 00:23:12,875
Can I trust her after all
the lies and deceit...?

528
00:23:12,958 --> 00:23:15,000
If I ask her if
she's on my side

529
00:23:15,083 --> 00:23:17,291
do I run the risk of
losing her forever...?

530
00:23:17,375 --> 00:23:18,541
No.

531
00:23:18,625 --> 00:23:20,041
You saved me...

532
00:23:20,125 --> 00:23:22,166
Thank you for
the protection.

533
00:23:22,250 --> 00:23:23,583
You're welcome.

534
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,041
Stop...!

535
00:23:31,125 --> 00:23:33,041
Hold on.

536
00:23:33,125 --> 00:23:34,541
Are you really
going home...?

537
00:23:34,625 --> 00:23:35,958
Please don't do that...

538
00:23:36,041 --> 00:23:38,250
Things there will never
be the same again.

539
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:40,458
I don't want you
to have to hurt.

540
00:23:40,541 --> 00:23:41,666
Let's go back...

541
00:23:41,750 --> 00:23:43,083
We'll go back to
your secret hideout

542
00:23:43,166 --> 00:23:44,125
and play games...

543
00:23:44,208 --> 00:23:45,375
As long as you want,

544
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:47,708
I'll stay right by your
side, Taku, I swear.

545
00:23:47,791 --> 00:23:49,958
We can walk to school together
and gossip with Daisuke

546
00:23:50,041 --> 00:23:51,333
about all the things
that are happening.

547
00:23:51,416 --> 00:23:52,666
You don't get it...

548
00:23:52,750 --> 00:23:54,625
It's Nanami,
I've got to see her.

549
00:23:54,708 --> 00:23:55,791
She's not there...

550
00:23:55,875 --> 00:23:57,375
She's gone.

551
00:23:57,458 --> 00:23:59,916
Taku... It hurts me
to see you sad...

552
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,666
Please don't go.

553
00:24:01,750 --> 00:24:03,958
Stop being so mysterious!

554
00:24:04,041 --> 00:24:06,708
Look, if there's a reason I
shouldn't go home, tell me...!

555
00:24:06,791 --> 00:24:07,708
Don't make me guess,

556
00:24:07,791 --> 00:24:08,916
I'm so sick and tired

557
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:12,125
of all this speaking
in riddles bullshit!

558
00:24:12,208 --> 00:24:13,125
Taku.

559
00:24:21,041 --> 00:24:22,583
This is the right street.

560
00:24:22,666 --> 00:24:24,166
Where is it...?

561
00:24:24,250 --> 00:24:25,541
Where's my house?

562
00:24:25,625 --> 00:24:27,083
Don't you get it, Taku...?

563
00:24:27,166 --> 00:24:29,250
There's no home in this
world for you to go to.

564
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:13,041
[Music]

565
00:26:43,250 --> 00:26:44,708
Those eyes...

566
00:26:44,791 --> 00:26:46,125
Whose are they?

